# Git commits — no Cursor co-author

When creating or amending git commits in this repository:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/agent co-author trailer.
- **Never** set the commit author or committer to `cursoragent@cursor.com` or `Cursor`.
- Commits must be attributed only to the human repository owner unless the user explicitly names a different human co-author.

If a tool or template suggests adding a Cursor co-author line, omit it.
